{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The rate of detections\/recognitions per second in energy save mode."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Defaults to 1, meaning that 1 frame per second is detected\/recognized."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When the video frame rate is 30, 29 frames will be skipped, 1 frame is detected\/recognized."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note: if you set the detection rate greater to or equal to the video frame rate, no frames will be skipped,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the actual detection rate is limited by the video frame rate."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note: Usually you set a much lower value here as for the detectionRate property to save energy."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK","doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@objc","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"dynamic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"energySaveDetectionRate","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UInt","preciseIdentifier":"s:Su","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerenergyconfiguration\/energysavedetectionrate"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerenergyconfiguration\/energysavedetectionrate"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","externalID":"c:@M@ScanbotSDK@objc(cs)SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration(py)energySaveDetectionRate","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"ScanbotSDK"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"energySaveDetectionRate","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"energySaveDetectionRate"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"energySaveDetectionRate"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UInt","preciseIdentifier":"s:Su"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration\/energySaveDetectionRate","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration":{"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerenergyconfiguration","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The energy management configuration object for a ‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and its subclasses."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and subclasses sport a customizable energy management system."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Since scanners running on a live video feed can put a lot of load onto the CPU and\/or GPU"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the device, causing the battery to drain quickly and running the device hot, you can customize the energy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consumption using this class by configuring the rate of detections\/recognitions per second in performance mode as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"well as in energy saving mode."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In performance mode the scanners will be fed with a higher, configurable rate of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"video frames per second."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After a certain, configurable period of inactivity the energy save mode will be engaged and the rate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of scans will be reduced to a lower (configurable) rate."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can also configure the time of inactivity before the automatic mode switches from performance to energy save mode."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Inactivity here means that both of the following conditions are met:"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration","type":"topic","title":"SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration/energySaveDetectionRate":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"energySaveDetectionRate"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The rate of detections\/recognitions per second in energy save mode."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Defaults to 1, meaning that 1 frame per second is detected\/recognized."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When the video frame rate is 30, 29 frames will be skipped, 1 frame is detected\/recognized."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note: if you set the detection rate greater to or equal to the video frame rate, no frames will be skipped,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the actual detection rate is limited by the video frame rate."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note: Usually you set a much lower value here as for the detectionRate property to save energy."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration\/energySaveDetectionR